TextSection.Contents: A rare spina bifida aperta malformation characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord and meninges from the spinal column into a fluid-filled sac at the location of the defect, resulting from incomplete closure of the primary neural tube. Clinical signs are variable, depending on location and severity of the lesion, but may include bladder and bowel dysfunction, hydrocephalus, and/or partial or complete paralysis of the lower limbs, among others.
